🔷 Understanding Request & Response

In this function:

```javascript
(req, res)
```

| Object | Purpose         |
| ------ | --------------- |
| req    | Client request  |
| res    | Server response |

Example:

```javascript
res.write("Hello");
res.end();
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Handling Different Routes

Node.js can respond differently depending on URL.

Example:

```javascript
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {

  if (req.url === "/") {
    res.write("Home Page");
  } 
  else if (req.url === "/about") {
    res.write("About Page");
  } 
  else {
    res.write("404 Page Not Found");
  }

  res.end();
});

server.listen(3000);
```

