🔷 Setting Response Headers

Headers tell the browser what type of data is sent.

Example:

```javascript
res.writeHead(200, { "Content-Type": "application/json" });
```

Example server:

```javascript
res.writeHead(200, { "Content-Type": "text/html" });
res.write("<h1>Hello</h1>");
res.end();
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 HTTP Status Codes

| Code | Meaning      |
| ---- | ------------ |
| 200  | Success      |
| 404  | Not Found    |
| 500  | Server Error |

Example:

```javascript
res.writeHead(404);
res.write("Page not found");
res.end();
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Example API Server

```javascript
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {

  if (req.url === "/api/users") {
    
    const users = [
      { id: 1, name: "John" },
      { id: 2, name: "Sarah" }
    ];

    res.writeHead(200, { "Content-Type": "application/json" });
    res.write(JSON.stringify(users));
  }

  res.end();
});

server.listen(3000);
```

